text: Kirsty Nicole Robb (born 23 May 1979) is a road cyclist from New Zealand. She represented her nation at the 1999, 2001, 2002 and 2003 UCI Road World Championships. ==References== ==External links== * profile at Procyclingstats.com Category:1979 births Category:New Zealand female cyclists Category:Living people Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
